commit.message:
Fix TS2322: timer ID type mismatch under Node.js typings (#804)

`globalThis.setTimeout` returns `NodeJS.Timeout` under Node typings but
`number` under DOM typings, causing `TS2322` errors when both
environments are present.

## Changes

- **`TimerProvider` interface** — `setTimeout` return and `clearTimeout`
parameter typed as `ReturnType<typeof globalThis.setTimeout>` instead of
`number`
- **`_disarmTimerId`** / **`timeoutId`** fields — same type update in
`confirmation-interlock-button.ts` and `toast-message.ts`
- **Test mock** — dummy timer ID returned via double-cast (`1 as unknown
as ReturnType<typeof globalThis.setTimeout>`) to satisfy type contract
without leaking real timers
- **`.at(-1)` reverted** — back to `arr[arr.length - 1]` to avoid ES2022
runtime dependency
- **Docstring** — `defaultTimerProvider` updated from "browser's native"
to "runtime's global"

```typescript
// Before
export interface TimerProvider {
  setTimeout(callback: () => void, delayMs: number): number;
  clearTimeout(id: number): void;
}

// After
export interface TimerProvider {
  setTimeout(callback: () => void, delayMs: number): ReturnType<typeof globalThis.setTimeout>;
  clearTimeout(id: ReturnType<typeof globalThis.setTimeout>): void;
}
```

